The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and the Minister of Foreign Affairs of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) in the Oval Office. President Trump praises the UAE as a great country with a great leader and expresses gratitude for their role in signing the recent agreement between Israel and the UAE. He believes that this agreement can lead to real peace in the Middle East. President Trump also mentions that other countries in the region will soon sign similar agreements. He addresses the issue of the Palestinians and states that they will likely join the agreement at some point, but other important countries will join first. President Trump also discusses Iran, saying that he believes a deal with Iran is possible after the U.S. election. He mentions that many other countries in the region are excited to normalize relations with Israel and that Bahrain is also signing the agreement. Overall, President Trump emphasizes the significance of the agreement and its positive impact on the Middle East.